HEADWORD: Felicitous
<hw>Fe*lic"i*tous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Characterized by
felicity; happy; prosperous; delightful; skillful; successful; happily
applied or expressed; appropriate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Felicitous</qex> words and images.</q> <rj><qau>M.
Arnold.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Fe*lic"i*tous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Fe*lic"i*tous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>felicitousness</ent>⟦br⟧
